<div style="background: lightblue; font-style: italic;">
   <h2>OneTime&nbsp;&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;&nbsp;Encryption with One-Time Pads</h2>
</div>

<h4><p style="margin-left: 10%; margin-right: 10%; color: red;
font-size: 80%;" >Update (2016-06-05): OneTime 2.0 is currently in
beta testing.  The latest version is <a href="onetime-2.0-beta7"
>2.0-beta7</a>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;please give it a try and
<a href="https://github.com/kfogel/OneTime/issues/new" >report</a>
any bugs you find.  See the <a href="changes" >compatibility notes</a>
for details about what's new in 2.0.</p></h4>

<a href="get" ><img style="float: left; margin-right: 3.5%;"
                    src="images/logo/onetime-logo-color-225x225.png" 
                    alt="OneTime logo" /></a>

<p><a href="onetime">OneTime</a> is an <a href="LICENSE" >open
source</a> encryption program that uses
the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One-time_pad">one-time
pad</a> algorithm to allow two parties to communicate privately.  It
has features to assist with the bureaucracy of pad management, and
comes with built-in <a href="#help" >help</a>.  OneTime requires
Python 2.6 or higher, and is for users who are comfortable running
command-line programs.  (It is not yet compatible with Python 3;
there's an open <a href="https://github.com/kfogel/OneTime/issues/15"
>ticket</a> for that, and patches are very welcome.)</p> 

